-1.title: Vivid Works, Art Deco Sweep Hat

episode of.title: Janette's I'm Every Woman! TV (TV Series 2016– )

-1.plot: Fashion and Flair. Hats are all the rage today and not just because the weather is getting cooler. Whatever the season, hats make a bold statement about who you are. In this Janette Recommends Must-Have Women's Products segment, Janette speaks with Raymond Atkinson of VIVID WORKS about the many art-deco hats, scarfs and hat pins that he and his partner create to frame your face, boost your confidence and enhance your style, day or night, where ever you wear them.

1.title: Olaf Jeglitza (O-Jay) and Karin Kasar, Founding Members of Euro/Dance/Pop Music Project Real McCoy

episode of.title: Janette's I'm Every Woman! TV (TV Series 2016– )

1.plot: Throughout the 90's sounds of German/Euro/Dance/Pop Music Project, Real McCoy, filled clubs and airwaves across Europe, Canada, the U.S. and Japan with Top-10 hits, "Another Night", "Automatic Lover", "Run Away", "One More Time," "Love and Devotion", and more. Real McCoy's ongoing popularity had founding members Olaf Jeglitza (O-Jay) and Karin Kasar reunite in 2006. They're still performing on world stages to thousands of raving fans today. 2.title: High Life with Robert Pattison and Mia Goth

episode of.title: Janette's I'm Every Woman! TV (TV Series 2016– )

2.plot: Janette catches-up with Master French filmmaker Claire Denis on the Tiff red carpet of her new movie High Life to talk about her long-anticipated English-language debut and provocative sci-fi drama starring Robert Pattinson, Mia Goth, Juliette Binoche, and André Benjamin as a group of criminals sent into deep space.

3.title: Liz Scott, The Business Firestarter, North America's Business Growth Guru

episode of.title: Janette's I'm Every Woman! TV (TV Series 2016– )

3.plot: Are you a woman in business struggling with your sales and marketing? In this Janette's I'm Every Woman. TV episode, Janette talks with The Business Firestarter, North America's Business Growth Guru, Liz Scott of Affinity Business Consulting, about the common pitfalls that hold women entrepreneurs back, how her experience can help you get your sales and marketing on track to break your first $50,000 and exceed far beyond, and much more.

5.title: Ron Finlay, Matrix Business Training Workshops

5.plot: What's the biggest challenge your face as a business owner? In this Janette's I'm Every Woman. TV episode, Janette speaks with owner of Matrix Business Training Workshops, Ron Finlay, about what does and doesn't work in business and why - so you can stop struggling.
